    <text id="B0017T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell requests a report on how many white people in Jackson's district who
                    need food but are not supplied by either the county or the Bureau.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen, and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Head Quarters 9th District
                    Department of the Potomac,
                    <name type="recipient">Mr Tho<hi rend="super">s</hi> P. Jackson<lb/>Agent<lb/>Staunton, Va.,</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-04-18">April 18th, 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, Va.</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>You will promptly report to this office the number of white persons in the
                    counties under your charge, who require supplies of food to prevent starvation
                    and extreme want, who are not now supplied by County authorities, and whose
                    cases are not properly included under the present regulations of the Bureau. the
                    number in each County will be given separately.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obdt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Servant">Svt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John A McDonnell<lb/>Captain V.R.C.<lb/>Sub <abbr expan="Assistant"
                            >Asst.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Commissioner">Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
